    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The First Congregational Church of New Village, built in 1818, was the community’s first church building.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        11
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lake_Grove%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The village’s name, adopted in the mid‑19th century, comes from the groves of trees near Lake Ronkonkoma.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        12
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lake_Grove%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The Ronkonkoma Moraine, a glacial ridge of gravel and boulders, shapes Lake Grove’s subtle elevations up to 200‑300 feet.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        4
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
